Q: Why is hybrid search better than vector-only search?

A: Hybrid search is better than vector-only search because it reduces the baseline failure rate significantly, providing more accurate and contextually relevant results. Specifically, a study shows that using a hybrid approach with a reranker reduces the retrieval failure rate from 5.7% to 1.9%, which represents a 67% reduction in failures compared to vector-only searches [1]. This improvement is attributed to the ability of hybrid systems to handle complex queries more effectively by leveraging both semantic understanding and exact match capabilities, thus connecting relevant pieces of information that might be missed by vector-only methods alone.

